wdi-GB.XPD.RSDV.GD.ZS.def: Gross domestic expenditures on research and development (R&D), expressed as a percent of GDP. They include both capital and current expenditures in the four main sectors: Business enterprise, Government, Higher education and Private non-profit. R&D covers basic research, applied research, and experimental development.
wdi-GB.XPD.RSDV.GD.ZS.name: Research and development expenditure
